response:
According to Section 59.5 and 59.6 of the master circular, stock brokers/trading members who provide the facility of algorithmic trading are required to subject their algorithmic trading system to a system audit every six months. The audit shall be conducted by a system auditor who possesses any of the following certifications: 

- CISA (Certified Information System Auditors) from ISACA;
- DISA (Post Qualification Certification in Information Systems Audit) from Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI);
- CISM (Certified Information Securities Manager) from ISACA;
- CISSP (Certified Information Systems Security Professional) from [unspecified organization].

The audit shall be reported to the Stock Exchange (SE) immediately on completion.
